<title>NETHERLANDS: KLM to convert two Combis to freighters.</title>
<headline>KLM to convert two Combis to freighters.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dutch airline KLM said on Thursday it had contracted Boeing to convert two of its 747-200 Combi aircraft to special freighters.</p>
<p>&quot;The new KLM 747 special freighters will be able to accommodate a maximum cargo payload of more than 100 tonnes. The Combi cannot carry more than 35 tonnes,&quot; KLM said in a statement.</p>
<p>The conversion will cost an estimated 40 million guilders per aircraft, KLM said.</p>
<p>It said the converted aircraft, the 747-200s &quot;Dr Albert Plesman&quot; and &quot;Wilbur Wright&quot; would operate on its major Europe-North America and Europe-Asia Pacific air freight routes.</p>
<p>The Plesman is due for conversion between late September 1997 and February 1998, while the Wilbur Wright will be converted in the period February to June 1998.</p>
